JOS â€“ Former INEC Resident Electoral Commissioner of Benue State Dr. Nentanwe Yilwatda has won the Plateau State APC Governorship ticket. Dr. Yilwatda polled a total of 803 votes to beat three other aspirants during the primary elections held at Landfield Park Rayfield. Other aspirants who participated in the election are Garba Pwul SAN who scored two votes, Deputy Governor of Plateau State Prof. Sonny Tyoden 25 votes and Hon. Victor David Dimka scored 7 Votes respectively. -Advertisement- Chairman of the Electoral Panel Committee, Rt. Hon. Habu Ajiya while declaring Dr. Nentawe Yilwatda winner of the election on Friday Morning in Jos explained that Nine Aspirants were in the race but five Aspirants later sent their letters of withdrawal from the contest . The affected Aspirant are Sunday Garba Biggs, Dr. Sarpiya Danyaro, Senator. Hezekiah Dimka, Dr. Patrick Dakum and Arch. Fitka. It would be recalled that the Deputy Governor, Professor Sonni Tyoden, Dr. Patrick Dakum and David Dimka had earlier staged a walk out just after about three Local Government delegates voted. However the Electoral Panel committee headed by Rt. Hon. Habub Ajiya described the governorship primaries election of the APC in the state that produce Yilwatda as the flagbearer of the Party as Peaceful, free and fair. Speaking after being declared the winner, Dr. Nentawe Yilwatda in his acceptance Speech pledged to ensure that the State is secure and united for more development if elected the Governor of the State. POLL He called on the other aspirants who contested with him to accord him the support for the goal of achieving a greater Plateau State. Dr. Yilwatda now APC Governorship Candidate is an Ngas by tribe from Kanke Local Government of the state and will now battle with the PDP Governorship Candidate Barr. Caleb Mutfwang from Mangu Local Government of the state at the 2023 General elections.